This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as machine translation. The paper also proposes a regularization technique to improve the performance of multi-head attention, which is a popular technique in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as regularization is a common technique in machine learning to prevent overfitting. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as multi-head attention is a popular technique in deep learning, which is a subfield of AI. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as multi-head attention has been applied to image processing tasks such as object detection and segmentation. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed regularization technique involves modifying the neural network architecture to improve its performance.
